Node.Notes: Tree assumes "[this is] the saying of Yahweh to my Lord:"
Uncertain. Maybe "willingness itself/voluntary offerings," in sense of volunteer/freely offer themselves.

Uncertain. Tree assumes "In holy array, from the womb of the dawn, the dew of your youth belongs to you," probably in sense like: majestically adorned, as fresh as the day at dawn, your young recruits gather themselves to you.
Probably figure of freshness and vigor.
Means "manner," generally translated "order" (in sense of line of succession), following the lead of the LXX.
Uncertain. Either "heads" literally or figure for rules.
Uncertain. To lift up the head is probably a sign of victory. See also ps3:3 and ps27:6.
